  "title": "Crane Operator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Operate mobile, crawler, or tower cranes according to approved lifting plans and safety procedures</li><li>Perform daily pre-operational checks and basic maintenance of crane equipment</li><li>Execute lifting operations in coordination with Lifting Supervisor, Rigger, and Signalman</li><li>Ensure all lifting activities comply with Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations</li><li>Follow load charts, rated capacities, and manufacturer’s operating instructions</li><li>Stop operations immediately if unsafe conditions are identified</li><li>Maintain accurate records for crane operations, inspections, and logbooks</li><li>Report equipment defects, incidents, or near-misses promptly</li><li>Support site operations as instructed by the Supervisor or Management</li></ul><p><strong>Safety & Compliance</strong></p><ul><li>Strictly adhere to WSH Act, MOM regulations, and company safety policies</li><li>Participate in toolbox meetings, safety briefings, and training sessions</li><li>Use appropriate PPE at all times on site</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Valid <strong>Crane Operator License</strong> issued by MOM /Accredited Authority</li><li>Minimum <strong>2–5 years</strong> of relevant crane operating experience (project-dependent)</li><li>Familiar with construction site operations and lifting procedures</li><li>Physically fit and medically certified for crane operation</li><li>Able to work overtime, weekends, and at multiple project sites when required</li><li>Team player with good safety awareness and discipline</li><li>preferrable able to work on shift works when required </li></ul>",
